{{Infobox Organization |name = Fédération des Entreprises Romandes Genève (FER Genève) |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |motto = |formation = 1929 |extinction = |type = [[Union of employers]] |headquarters = 98, rue de Saint-Jean, 1201 Genève |location = [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]] |membership = |language = |leader_title = General Director |leader_name = Blaise Matthey |key_people = |num_staff = |budget = |website = [http://www.fer-ge.ch] }} The '''Fédération des Entreprises Romandes Genève''' (FER Genève) is a Swiss (''Romand'' designates Swiss cantons where people speak French) [[Employer's organization|employer’s organization]] based in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]]. It groups 27&nbsp;000 members, including [[multinational corporations]] as well as 9000 independent workers and 80 [[trade associations]]. It is involved in negotiations with the [[trade unions]], political [[lobbying]] and the provision of services and [[business networking]] opportunities for its members.<ref>Eric Rabbath, « La Fédération des syndicats patronaux à Genève va changer de nom », ''L’AGEFI'', 17 september 2003</ref><ref>Serge Guertchakoff, « La Fédération des syndicats patronaux change de nom », ''La [[Tribune de Genève]]'', 17 march 2003</ref>
The FER Genève operates two institutions active in the [[Pension system in Switzerland|Swiss pension system]]: CIAM-AVS (active in the first pillar of the system) and the CIEPP (active in the second pillar).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fer-ge.ch/web/fer-ge/assurances-sociales/ |title=FER Genève |language=fr |publisher=Secure1.fer-ge.ch |date= |accessdate=2014-01-09}}</ref>
