{{for|the Swedish footballer|Mats Jansson (footballer)}}
'''Mats Jansson''' (born 1951, in [[Kolsva]], [[Sweden]]) is a Swedish [[businessperson]]. He was [[Chief Executive Officer]] of [[SAS Group]] from 2007 to 2010.<ref>[http://www.affarsvarlden.se/hem/nyheter/article273850.ece ''Mats Jansson ny vd i SAS''], [[Affärsvärlden]] 2006-10-16 {{sv icon}}</ref> <ref>[http://www.svd.se/naringsliv/sas-chefen-mats-jansson-slutar_5113071.svd ''SAS-chefen Mats Jansson slutar''], [[Svenska Dagbladet]] 2010-08-10 {{sv icon}}</ref>
==Biography== Jansson was educated in [[economics]] and [[sociology]] at the [[Örebro University]], before he started a career in [[ICA AB|ICA]], where he held a range of senior positions from 1973 to 1994. He then worked as CEO of {{Interlanguage link multi|Catena AB|sv|lt=Catena}} until 1999 when he was hired as CEO of [[Fazer Group]]. In 2000 he became CEO of [[Axfood]] and in 2005 Chairman of the company while changing to CEO of [[Axel Johnson]]. He was hired as CEO of SAS Group in 2007. Jansson is married and has three kids, and lives in switzerland.
